+# Change Summary: toolchain-and-types
+
+> Auto-generated summary after all waves complete.
+
+---
+
+## Intent
+
+Bootstrap the npm + TypeScript toolchain for the sokoban project so all later changes (c2: build/test configs, c3: canvas entry, c4: smoke test, plus all 9 later phases) can build, lint, and run on a known foundation. Required prerequisite for the entire project.
+
+## Output Files
+
+| File | Action |
+|------|--------|
+| `.gitignore` | Create |
+| `.nvmrc` | Create |
+| `tsconfig.json` | Create |
+| `tsconfig.node.json` | Create |
+| `package.json` | Create |
+| `package-lock.json` | Create (via `npm install`) |
+
+## Key Decisions
+
+- **Pinned versions match research** (`bp/research/stack.md` Final Selection table): vite 8.1.2, vitest 4.1.9, happy-dom 20.10.6, typescript 5.9.3 (within `^5.6.3` semver), @types/node 20.19.43 (within `^20.19.0`).
+- **Strict TypeScript from day one**: `strict: true`, `noUncheckedIndexedAccess: true`, `noImplicitOverride: true`, `verbatimModuleSyntax: true` — catches untyped grid-coordinate accesses early; aligns with the architecture research's recommendation that `core/` modules stay pure and tightly typed.
+- **ESM throughout**: `"type": "module"` + `moduleResolution: "bundler"` — required for `import.meta.glob` typing in ph.3 level loader; matches Vite 8 defaults.
+- **Project references via `tsconfig.node.json`**: separate composite project for Vite/Vitest config files using `@types/node`. Standard Vite 8 pattern.
+- **`.nvmrc` pins 20.19.0**: Vite 8 minimum; explicit so future contributors match.
+- **`engines.node`: `>=20.19.0`** in `package.json`: hard guard against older Node; npm refuses install on unsupported versions.
+
+## Verification Results
+
+- Type check (main project): **`npx tsc --noEmit` exits 0** — strict mode loads cleanly against empty `src/` and `tests/`.
+- Type check (composite build): `npx tsc -b` fails with `TS18003: No inputs were found in config file 'tsconfig.node.json'` — **expected** because `vite.config.ts` / `vitest.config.ts` don't exist yet. Resolved by c2. The build script `tsc -b && vite build` will work end-to-end after c2.
+- Tests: no tests in this change; c4 (`smoke-test`) is the first test-bearing change. `npm test` would currently fail because `vitest.config.ts` doesn't exist — expected.
+- Lint: not configured yet (ph.9).
+- Installed packages: 54 packages added via `npm install`; `package-lock.json` is 46 KB.
+- Tool versions verified: `vite/8.1.2`, `vitest/4.1.9`, `typescript/5.9.3`, `happy-dom/20.10.6`, `@types/node/20.19.43`.
+
+## Verification Commands Run
+
+```bash
+node --version          # v26.3.1 (≥ 20.19.0 minimum ✓)
+npm install             # exit 0; 54 packages
+npx tsc --noEmit        # exit 0
+npx tsc -b              # exit 1 (expected; c2 will fix)
+node_modules/.bin/tsc --version    # Version 5.9.3
+node_modules/.bin/vite --version   # 8.1.2
+node_modules/.bin/vitest --version # 4.1.9
+```
+
+## Readiness for c2
+
+c2 (`vite-vitest-configs`) is unblocked: it depends only on `package.json` + `npm install` having completed, both of which this change delivered. c2 will create `vite.config.ts` and `vitest.config.ts`, at which point `tsc -b` will succeed and `npm run build` will produce `dist/`.
+
+c3 (`entry-canvas`) is also unblocked at the dependency level — but `tsc --noEmit` on its `src/main.ts` will fail until c2 supplies `vite.config.ts` (because the main tsconfig references `tsconfig.node.json`). c3 should be applied after c2.
\ No newline at end of file
