+# Context: ph.1-foundation
+
+> Phase: ph.1-foundation  |  Milestone: M1-core-playable  |  Mode: mvp
+> Goal: Establish the toolchain and empty canvas shell that all later phases build on.
+> Deliverable: `npm run dev` boots a browser with a blank `<canvas>` showing the project title. `npm test` runs Vitest with one smoke test. `npm run build` produces a `dist/`.
+
+## Locked Decisions
+
+### D1: Toolchain versions (frozen per `bp/research/stack.md`)
+- **Decision**: Vite ^8.1.2, TypeScript ^5.6, Vitest ^4.1.9, happy-dom ^20.10.6, npm.
+- **Rationale**: Verified against npm registry on 2026-07-01; all peer-compatible; Node 20.19+ required by Vite 8.
+- **Alternatives considered**: Vite ^7 (fallback if Node pin is older); esbuild; Parcel.
+- **Impact**: `package.json` devDeps, `.nvmrc` (20.19.0), all configs.
+
+### D2: Project file layout (per `bp/research/architecture.md` file-tree sketch)
+- **Decision**: `index.html` at root; `src/main.ts` entry; `src/core/`, `src/level/`, `src/state/`, `src/render/`, `src/input/`, `src/anim/`, `src/storage/`, `src/ui/`, `src/shell/`, `src/types.ts` as future module homes (created empty or as needed); `tests/unit/` and `tests/e2e/` for tests.
+- **Rationale**: Matches architecture research; module boundaries enforced early.
+- **Alternatives considered**: Flat `src/` layout (rejected — no module boundaries).
+- **Impact**: All subsequent phases' file creation.
+
+### D3: `tsconfig.json` settings (locked per research)
+- **Decision**: `moduleResolution: 'bundler'`, `target: 'ES2022'`, `strict: true`, `module: 'ESNext'`, `lib: ['ES2022', 'DOM']`, `types: ['vite/client']`, `noUncheckedIndexedAccess: true`, `noImplicitOverride: true`.
+- **Rationale**: `'bundler'` enables `import.meta.glob` typing; `strict + noUncheckedIndexedAccess` catch the bugs most likely in game-loop code (untyped grid accesses).
+- **Alternatives considered**: Looser strictness; `nodenext` module resolution (rejected — incompatible with Vite `import.meta.glob` ergonomics).
+- **Impact**: All subsequent TS files must pass strict checks before commit.
+
+### D4: `vite.config.ts` — env-driven base
+- **Decision**: `base: process.env.GH_PAGES_BASE ?? '/'` for ph.1 (env-driven shape established; production value set in ph.9 to `/sokoban/`).
+- **Rationale**: Matches pitfalls BLOCKER #11; ph.1 only needs the shape so ph.9 just flips the default.
+- **Alternatives considered**: Hardcoded `/`; hardcoded `/sokoban/`.
+- **Impact**: All asset URL decisions in later phases.
+
+### D5: `vitest.config.ts` — scoped DOM environment
+- **Decision**: Default env = `node`; use `environmentMatchGlobs: [['tests/**/*-dom.test.ts', 'happy-dom']]` for DOM-touching tests. Pure logic tests stay in `node` (faster).
+- **Rationale**: Happy-dom is faster than jsdom; pure game-logic tests need no DOM at all.
+- **Alternatives considered**: Always happy-dom; always jsdom; always node.
+- **Impact**: All test files in later phases; naming convention `-dom.test.ts` for DOM-touching tests.
+
+### D6: `index.html` — canvas + HUD placeholder
+- **Decision**: Single `<canvas id="game">` element plus a minimal `<div id="hud">` overlay (move count, level name placeholder). Static HTML; no bundler-rendered template.
+- **Rationale**: Matches architecture research (HUD as DOM, game world as Canvas); allows CSS-driven responsive layout from ph.6.
+- **Alternatives considered**: HUD drawn on canvas (rejected — complicates responsive resize).
+- **Impact**: All UI work in M2.
+
+### D7: Smoke test placeholder
+- **Decision**: `tests/unit/smoke.test.ts` with one trivial assertion (e.g., `expect(1 + 1).toBe(2)`) to confirm Vitest boots.
+- **Rationale**: Verifies the test runner is wired correctly without committing to any game-logic shape; ph.2 replaces with real tests.
+- **Alternatives considered**: No tests in ph.1 (rejected — leaves `npm test` undefined as a script).
+- **Impact**: `tests/unit/smoke.test.ts` removed/replaced in ph.2.
+
+### D8: `.gitignore` baseline
+- **Decision**: `node_modules/`, `dist/`, `.DS_Store`, `coverage/`, `playwright-report/`, `test-results/`, `.env*` (allow `.env.example`).
+- **Rationale**: Standard for Vite + Vitest + Playwright projects.
+- **Alternatives considered**: — (no realistic alternative).
+- **Impact**: All generated artifacts ignored.
+
+## Gray Areas (Unresolved)
+
+None. All decisions clear from `bp/requirements.md`, `bp/research/stack.md`, `bp/research/architecture.md`, and `bp/roadmap.md`. Express path taken per user direction.
+
+## Deferred Ideas
+
+- ESLint / Prettier setup — deferred to ph.9 (CI/CD phase) where it pairs naturally with the lint step in `ci.yml`.
+- Conventional Commits enforcement (husky + commitlint) — deferred to ph.9.
+- Vite `base` production default value `/sokoban/` — ph.1 sets the env-driven shape; ph.9 flips the default to the GitHub Pages sub-path.
+- Conventional Commits / branch protection — not in ph.1 scope; added in M3.
+
+## Non-Goals
+
+- Any game logic (move, push, win, undo) — belongs to ph.2.
+- Any level data — belongs to ph.3.
+- Any keyboard/touch input handling — belongs to ph.3+.
+- Any renderer beyond a blank canvas — belongs to ph.3.
+- Linting / formatting setup — belongs to ph.9.
+- E2E / Playwright — belongs to ph.8.
+- Deployment / CI — belongs to ph.9.
+- Conventional Commits enforcement — belongs to ph.9.
+- Conventional PR / branch policy — not in any phase.
