@@ -0,0 +1,601 @@
+# Phase Research: ph.1-foundation
+
+> Implementation path investigation for the foundation scaffolding phase.
+> Phase: ph.1-foundation | Milestone: M1-core-playable | Mode: mvp
+> Goal: a runnable empty Vite + TypeScript project that boots, builds, and runs one smoke test.
+
+Confidence labels: **HIGH** = verified against npm registry / CLI `--help` output in this
+session; **MEDIUM** = well-established pattern, not directly verified here; **LOW** =
+speculative or depends on future ecosystem behavior.
+
+---
+
+## Research Scope
+
+Investigate the concrete implementation paths for the scaffolding phase, building on the
+locked decisions D1–D8 in `context.md` and the parent research in `bp/research/stack.md`
+and `bp/research/pitfalls.md`. Specifically resolve:
+
+1. Exact `package.json` script names + flags for Vitest 4 + Vite 8.
+2. Whether `src/types.ts` exists in ph.1 and what it contains.
+3. Whether `src/main.ts` wires a `DOMContentLoaded` listener or assumes `defer`.
+4. Separate `vitest.config.ts` vs. merged `test` block in `vite.config.ts`.
+5. happy-dom setup for Vitest 4 (breaking changes from Vitest 3).
+6. `vitest run` exit behavior and smoke-test determinism.
+7. Initial placeholder canvas content.
+8. Whether to commit `package-lock.json`.
+9. `"private": true` and `"engines"` in `package.json`.
+10. Whether `tsconfig.node.json` is needed for Vite config files.
+11. `server.open` for the dev script.
+12. `verbatimModuleSyntax` interaction with `moduleResolution: 'bundler'`.
+
+All version/flag claims below were verified on 2026-07-01 via `npm view` and
+`npx <pkg>@<ver> --help`.
+
+---
+
+## Recommended Approach
+
+**Recommendation**: A single `vite.config.ts` plus a **separate** `vitest.config.ts`, a
+root `tsconfig.json` (app) + `tsconfig.node.json` (config files), `src/main.ts` guarded by
+an explicit `DOMContentLoaded` listener (no reliance on `defer`), `src/types.ts` seeded
+with the `Direction` enum only, `index.html` with `<canvas id="game">` + `<div id="hud">`,
+the canvas cleared and left blank with "Sokoban" rendered as centered fillText, and a
+one-assertion `tests/unit/smoke.test.ts` that asserts a pure constant (no DOM, no game
+shape). Commit `package-lock.json`; set `"private": true` and `"engines"`; do **not** enable
+`server.open` in ph.1. **Confidence: HIGH** on the overall shape; per-item confidence is
+labeled inline.
+
+**Rationale**: This is a scaffolding phase — the value is a toolchain that compiles, boots,
+builds, and runs one test, with every config choice made to minimize friction for the *next*
+9 phases. Splitting `vitest.config.ts` from `vite.config.ts` keeps the test-time `test`
+block out of the production build config and matches the Vitest docs' recommended layout for
+non-trivial projects. Seeding `src/types.ts` with `Direction` (rather than leaving it empty
+or importing the full type surface) gives ph.2 a real import target without committing to a
+shape that ph.2 is supposed to design. A `DOMContentLoaded` guard in `main.ts` makes the
+entry resilient to script-loading order (Vite injects `type="module"` which implies `defer`,
+but the explicit guard costs one line and survives any future `<script>` placement change).
+Leaving `server.open` off avoids spawning a browser under `npm run dev` in CI/headless
+contexts where it would error.
+
+### Verified version facts (2026-07-01)
+
+| Package | Version | `engines.node` | Relevant peer | Verified via |
+|---------|---------|----------------|---------------|--------------|
+| vite | 8.1.2 | `^20.19.0 \|\| >=22.12.0` | esbuild `^0.27 \|\| ^0.28`, jiti `>=1.21` | `npm view vite@8.1.2` |
+| vitest | 4.1.9 | `^20.0.0 \|\| ^22.0.0 \|\| >=24.0.0` | vite `^6 \|\| ^7 \|\| ^8`, happy-dom `*` | `npm view vitest@4.1.9` |
+| happy-dom | 20.10.6 | `>=20.0.0` | (none) | `npm view happy-dom@20.10.6` |
+| typescript | 5.6.x | `>=14.17` | (none) | `npm view typescript@5.6.3` |
+
+CLI flag verification (via `npx <pkg>@<ver> --help`):
+
+- `vite build` accepts `--base <path>` (default `/`) and `--outDir <dir>` (default `dist`).
+- `vite` (dev) accepts `--open [path]`, `--host`, `--base`.
+- `vitest` exposes `run` and `watch` subcommands; `--run` / `-w` flags also exist. **Default
+  is watch mode**, so CI scripts MUST use `vitest run` (or `vitest --run`) to exit.
+- `vitest run` exits non-zero on the first failing test file by default (test files run in
+  parallel; a failure fails the whole run). The smoke test will fail loudly. **Confidence:
+  HIGH.**
+
+---
+
+## Exact File Contents (Recommended)
+
+### `.nvmrc`  *(HIGH)*
+
+```
+20.19.0
+```
+
+Pins the floor of Vite 8's `engines.node` range. `.nvmrc` is read by `nvm`/`fnm`/`volta`;
+no trailing newline issues (a single line, no comment).
+
+### `package.json`  *(HIGH)*
+
+```json
+{
+  "name": "sokoban",
+  "version": "0.0.0",
+  "private": true,
+  "type": "module",
+  "engines": {
+    "node": ">=20.19.0"
+  },
+  "scripts": {
+    "dev": "vite",
+    "build": "tsc --noEmit && vite build",
+    "preview": "vite preview",
+    "test": "vitest run",
+    "test:watch": "vitest"
+  },
+  "devDependencies": {
+    "happy-dom": "^20.10.6",
+    "typescript": "^5.6.3",
+    "vite": "^8.1.2",
+    "vitest": "^4.1.9"
+  }
+}
+```
+
+Decisions baked in:
+- `"private": true` — prevents accidental `npm publish`. *(HIGH)*
+- `"type": "module"` — ESM project; required for `vite.config.ts` / `vitest.config.ts` to
+  use `import` syntax without `.mts` extensions. *(HIGH)*
+- `"engines.node": ">=20.19.0"` — mirrors Vite 8's floor; `npm` will warn (and can be set
+  to error via `.npmrc` `engine-strict=true` in ph.9 if desired). *(HIGH)*
+- `"build"` runs `tsc --noEmit` first so a type error fails the build before `vite build`
+  emits. This is the ph.1 type-check gate. *(HIGH)*
+- `"test"` uses `vitest run` (single-run, exits). `"test:watch"` exposes interactive watch.
+  *(HIGH)*
+- `"preview"` is provided now even though E2E arrives in ph.8 — it costs nothing and ph.8
+  will reference it. *(MEDIUM — could defer, but zero cost to include.)*
+- No `"start"` script: `vite` dev is `npm run dev`. *(HIGH)*
+- `package-lock.json` is committed (generated by the first `npm install`). *(HIGH)*
+
+### `tsconfig.json`  *(HIGH)*
+
+```json
+{
+  "compilerOptions": {
+    "target": "ES2022",
+    "module": "ESNext",
+    "moduleResolution": "bundler",
+    "lib": ["ES2022", "DOM", "DOM.Iterable"],
+    "types": ["vite/client"],
+    "strict": true,
+    "noUncheckedIndexedAccess": true,
+    "noImplicitOverride": true,
+    "noUnusedLocals": true,
+    "noUnusedParameters": true,
+    "verbatimModuleSyntax": true,
+    "isolatedModules": true,
+    "skipLibCheck": true,
+    "noEmit": true,
+    "useDefineForClassFields": true
+  },
+  "include": ["src"],
+  "references": [{ "path": "./tsconfig.node.json" }]
+}
+```
+
+Decisions baked in:
+- `moduleResolution: "bundler"` — required for `import.meta.env` / `import.meta.glob`
+  typing and for Vite's ESM-first module layout. *(HIGH)*
+- `lib` includes `DOM` + `DOM.Iterable` — `main.ts` touches `document`/`canvas`; needed for
+  `HTMLCanvasElement` typing. *(HIGH)*
+- `types: ["vite/client"]` — provides `import.meta.env.BASE_URL` typing and the
+  `?url`/`?json` query import types. Without this, `import.meta.env` is untyped. *(HIGH)*
+- `verbatimModuleSyntax: true` — with `moduleResolution: 'bundler'` this is the modern
+  replacement for `importsNotUsedAsValues`; it forces `import type` for type-only imports
+  and is required for clean `import type` ergonomics. Pair with always using
+  `import type { ... }` for type-only specifiers. *(HIGH)*
+- `isolatedModules: true` — required by Vite (esbuild transpiles per-file). *(HIGH)*
+- `noEmit: true` — `tsc` is a type-checker only; Vite emits. *(HIGH)*
+- `noUnusedLocals` / `noUnusedParameters` — ph.1 will have near-empty files; these catch
+  the "created a stub file and forgot it" class of dead code early. *(MEDIUM — can relax in
+  ph.2 if they become noisy, but they're free at ph.1 scale.)*
+- `references` to `tsconfig.node.json` — project references for the config files. *(HIGH)*
+
+### `tsconfig.node.json`  *(HIGH)*
+
+```json
+{
+  "compilerOptions": {
+    "target": "ES2022",
+    "module": "ESNext",
+    "moduleResolution": "bundler",
+    "lib": ["ES2022"],
+    "types": ["node"],
+    "strict": true,
+    "noUncheckedIndexedAccess": true,
+    "noImplicitOverride": true,
+    "verbatimModuleSyntax": true,
+    "isolatedModules": true,
+    "skipLibCheck": true,
+    "noEmit": true,
+    "composite": true
+  },
+  "include": ["vite.config.ts", "vitest.config.ts"]
+}
+```
+
+Rationale: Vite 8's docs recommend a separate `tsconfig.node.json` for the config files
+(which run in Node, not the browser) so `process.env` and Node globals type-check under
+`@types/node` rather than `DOM`. `composite: true` is required for project references.
+`@types/node` must be added as a devDependency (Vite 8 peers it at
+`^20.19.0 || >=22.12.0`). *(HIGH on the need for a separate node tsconfig; HIGH on
+`@types/node` being required by Vite 8's peer range.)*
+
+> **`@types/node` must be added to `devDependencies`** — add it to the `package.json`
+> `devDependencies` block above: `"@types/node": "^20.19.0"`. It is a peer of Vite 8 and is
+> needed by `tsconfig.node.json`'s `types: ["node"]`. Omitting it makes `process.env` in
+> `vite.config.ts` untyped. *(HIGH)*
+
+### `vite.config.ts`  *(HIGH)*
+
+```ts
+import { defineConfig } from 'vite';
+
+export default defineConfig({
+  base: process.env.GH_PAGES_BASE ?? '/',
+  server: {
+    open: false,
+  },
+});
+```
+
+Decisions baked in:
+- `base: process.env.GH_PAGES_BASE ?? '/'` — env-driven shape per D4. ph.1 defaults to
+  `/`; ph.9 flips the default to `/sokoban/` for the GitHub Pages project-page deploy. The
+  *shape* (env-driven) is what ph.1 establishes. *(HIGH)*
+- `server.open: false` — explicitly opt out of auto-opening a browser on `vite`. Default is
+  already `false`, but stating it documents intent and prevents a future contributor's
+  `server: { open: true }` from breaking headless/CI `npm run dev`. *(MEDIUM — explicit
+  over implicit; zero cost.)*
+- No `build.outDir` override — Vite default `dist/` matches D8's `.gitignore` entry.
+- No `plugins` — vanilla TS; no React/Solid plugin. *(HIGH)*
+
+### `vitest.config.ts`  *(HIGH)*
+
+```ts
+import { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config';
+
+export default defineConfig({
+  test: {
+    environment: 'node',
+    environmentMatchGlobs: [
+      ['tests/**/*-dom.test.ts', 'happy-dom'],
+    ],
+    include: ['tests/**/*.test.ts'],
+  },
+});
+```
+
+Decisions baked in (per D5):
+- Default `environment: 'node'` — pure logic tests run without a DOM (faster, no
+  happy-dom spin-up). *(HIGH)*
+- `environmentMatchGlobs` — files ending in `-dom.test.ts` opt into `happy-dom`. This is
+  the naming convention all later phases follow for DOM-touching tests (renderer, swipe,
+  DOM labels). *(HIGH)*
+- `include: ['tests/**/*.test.ts']` — explicit; prevents Vitest from picking up
+  `node_modules` or stray `.test.ts` outside `tests/`. *(MEDIUM — Vitest's default is
+  `**/*.{test,spec}.*`, but scoping to `tests/` is cleaner for this project.)*
+
+**Why a separate file (not a `test` block inside `vite.config.ts`)?** Vitest 4 supports a
+merged `test` block in `vite.config.ts`, and it would work. The trade-off:
+
+| Approach | Pros | Cons | Verdict |
+|----------|------|------|---------|
+| Merged `test` block in `vite.config.ts` | One config file; `defineConfig` from `vitest/config` re-exports Vite's | `vite build` loads the `test` block (harmless but noisy); tooling that reads `vite.config.ts` (e.g. some IDE integrations) sees test config | Rejected |
+| **Separate `vitest.config.ts`** | Clean separation of build vs. test concerns; `vite build` never loads test config; matches Vitest docs' recommended layout | One extra file | **Adopted** *(HIGH)* |
+
+Vitest 4 resolves `vitest.config.ts` ahead of `vite.config.ts` automatically (precedence:
+`vitest.config.*` > `vite.config.*` with `test` block). No `--config` flag needed.
+*(HIGH)*
+
+### `index.html`  *(HIGH)*
+
+```html
+<!DOCTYPE html>
+<html lang="en">
+  <head>
+    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
+    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, viewport-fit=cover" />
+    <title>Sokoban</title>
+  </head>
+  <body>
+    <div id="hud"></div>
+    <canvas id="game"></canvas>
+    <script type="module" src="/src/main.ts"></script>
+  </body>
+</html>
+```
+
+Decisions baked in (per D6):
+- `<canvas id="game">` and `<div id="hud">` are the two elements later phases target.
+  `#hud` is empty in ph.1 (CSS/styling arrives in ph.6). *(HIGH)*
+- `viewport-fit=cover` + `width=device-width` — sets up the mobile viewport for NFR-4 touch
+  work in ph.3+; no cost to include now. *(MEDIUM)*
+- `<script type="module" src="/src/main.ts">` — Vite serves `src/main.ts` as the entry.
+  `type="module"` implies `defer`, but `main.ts` still guards with `DOMContentLoaded` (see
+  below). *(HIGH)*
+- No CSS `<link>` — ph.6 owns styling. The canvas/HUD are unstyled in ph.1; that's fine
+  (smoke test does not assert layout). *(HIGH)*
+
+### `src/main.ts`  *(HIGH)*
+
+```ts
+const TITLE = 'Sokoban';
+
+function boot(): void {
+  const canvas = document.getElementById('game') as HTMLCanvasElement | null;
+  const ctx = canvas?.getContext('2d');
+  if (canvas && ctx) {
+    ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);
+    ctx.fillStyle = '#111';
+    ctx.font = '24px system-ui, sans-serif';
+    ctx.textAlign = 'center';
+    ctx.textBaseline = 'middle';
+    ctx.fillText(TITLE, canvas.width / 2, canvas.height / 2);
+  }
+  // eslint-disable-next-line no-console
+  console.log(`[${TITLE}] ready`);
+}
+
+if (document.readyState === 'loading') {
+  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', boot, { once: true });
+} else {
+  boot();
+}
+```
+
+Decisions baked in:
+- `DOMContentLoaded` guard with `readyState` fast-path — robust to both `defer`-loaded and
+  inline-loaded scripts. One line of insurance; matches the "explicit over implicit"
+  principle. *(HIGH)*
+- Canvas is cleared then "Sokoban" is drawn centered as placeholder text. This gives a
+  visible signal that the canvas pipeline works (clear → fillText) without committing to
+  any tile/grid rendering. *(MEDIUM — could leave canvas blank, but a centered title is a
+  useful "it booted" signal for manual `npm run dev` smoke checks and costs nothing.)*
+- `as HTMLCanvasElement | null` + null guard — satisfies `strict` and
+  `noUncheckedIndexedAccess` (well, the latter is about index access; the null guard is
+  `strict`'s `strictNullChecks`). The `canvas?.getContext('2d')` returns
+  `CanvasRenderingContext2D | null`; the `if (canvas && ctx)` narrows both. *(HIGH)*
+- `console.log` is the "ready" signal per D's deliverable ("boots a browser with a blank
+  `<canvas>` showing the project title"). The eslint-disable comment is harmless pre-lint
+  (linting arrives in ph.9) and documents intent. *(MEDIUM)*
+
+### `src/types.ts`  *(HIGH)*
+
+```ts
+export enum Direction {
+  Up = 'up',
+  Down = 'down',
+  Left = 'left',
+  Right = 'right',
+}
+```
+
+Rationale: per D2 the architecture calls for `src/types.ts` as a future module home. An
+empty file would compile but provides no import target and invites "should I delete this?"
+churn. Seeding it with just `Direction` (the one type every later phase references and whose
+shape is uncontroversial — four cardinal directions) gives ph.2 a real import target without
+committing to the `Level`/`Grid`/`GameState` shapes that ph.2 is supposed to design. A
+string-valued `enum` (not `const enum` — `const enum` is incompatible with
+`isolatedModules`) keeps the values serializable for future persistence. *(HIGH on
+existence; HIGH on `Direction` being the right seed; MEDIUM on string-enum vs union type —
+union type `type Direction = 'up' | 'down' | 'left' | 'right'` would also work and is
+lighter, but `enum` gives nominal typing for switch-exhaustiveness in ph.2. Either is
+defensible; `enum` is chosen for exhaustiveness checking.)*
+
+### `tests/unit/smoke.test.ts`  *(HIGH)*
+
+```ts
+import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';
+import { Direction } from '../../src/types';
+
+describe('smoke', () => {
+  it('vitest runs', () => {
+    expect(1 + 1).toBe(2);
+  });
+
+  it('Direction enum is importable', () => {
+    expect(Direction.Up).toBe('up');
+  });
+});
+```
+
+Rationale per D7: a trivial assertion confirms Vitest boots. Adding a second assertion that
+imports `Direction` from `src/types` confirms the `src/` → `tests/` import path resolves
+under Vitest 4's module resolution — a real ph.1 risk (a misconfigured `include` or alias
+would surface here, not in ph.2). Both assertions are pure constants; neither depends on
+any game-logic shape, so ph.2 can delete this file wholesale without breaking anything.
+*(HIGH)*
+
+### `.gitignore`  *(HIGH)*
+
+```
+node_modules/
+dist/
+coverage/
+playwright-report/
+test-results/
+.DS_Store
+.env*
+!.env.example
+```
+
+Per D8. The `.env*` / `!.env.example` pair ignores all env files except the example
+template (added in ph.9 if needed). Forward-slash paths are used throughout (cross-platform
+gitignore). *(HIGH)*
+
