+
+## Alternatives Considered
+
+| Approach | Pros | Cons | Verdict |
+|----------|------|------|---------|
+| **A: Separate `vitest.config.ts` + `tsconfig.node.json` + DOMContentLoaded guard + seeded `types.ts`** | Clean separation of build/test concerns; Node-typed config files; resilient entry; real import target for ph.2 | Two extra config files vs. one | **Adopted** *(HIGH)* |
+| B: Merged `test` block in `vite.config.ts`, single `tsconfig.json`, rely on `defer`, empty `types.ts` | One fewer config file; minimal | `vite build` loads test config; `process.env` untyped in config files; entry brittle to script placement; ph.2 has no import target and must create `types.ts` anyway | Rejected *(HIGH)* |
+| C: `vite.config.ts` only (no `vitest.config.ts`), `tsconfig.node.json` present, rely on `defer` | Middle ground | Still merges test into build config; no clean test-time-only knobs | Rejected *(HIGH)* |
+| D: Empty `src/types.ts` (zero content) | Truly minimal scaffolding | Compiles but is dead code; ph.2 recreates it; risks "why does this empty file exist?" churn | Rejected *(HIGH — seeding `Direction` is strictly better)* |
+| E: `src/types.ts` with full type surface (`Level`, `Grid`, `Tile`, `GameState`, `Box`, `Player`) | Ph.2 has everything ready | Commits ph.2 to a shape it's supposed to design; violates "ph.1 is scaffolding, no game logic" | Rejected *(HIGH)* |
+| F: Canvas left fully blank (no "Sokoban" fillText) | Slightly less code | No visible "it booted" signal; manual smoke check shows a blank page with no feedback | Rejected *(MEDIUM — blank is defensible but the centered title is a better smoke signal)* |
+| G: `server.open: true` in `vite.config.ts` | Auto-opens browser on `npm run dev` | Breaks headless/CI `npm run dev`; surprising in WSL/remote dev | Rejected *(HIGH)* |
+| H: `const enum Direction` instead of `enum` | Slightly smaller emit | `const enum` is incompatible with `isolatedModules: true` (Vite/esbuild transpile per-file); would require `--preserveConstEnums` and breaks cross-module `const enum` inlining | Rejected *(HIGH)* |
+| I: Union type `type Direction = 'up' \| 'down' \| 'left' \| 'right'` instead of `enum` | Lighter; no emit; trivially serializable | Loses nominal typing and switch-exhaustiveness checking that `enum` gives in ph.2's reducer | Acceptable alternative *(MEDIUM)* — `enum` chosen for exhaustiveness, but union is a valid ph.2 refactor |
+
