+
+## Known Pitfalls
+
+- **Vite 8 / Vitest 4 / happy-dom peer ranges.** Verified: `vitest@4.1.9` peers
+  `vite ^6||^7||^8` and `happy-dom *`; `vite@8.1.2` peers `esbuild ^0.27||^0.28` and
+  `jiti >=1.21` (both auto-resolved by npm). `@types/node ^20.19.0 || >=22.12.0` is a
+  **peer of Vite 8** — it MUST be in devDependencies or `process.env` in `vite.config.ts`
+  is untyped. *(HIGH — verified via `npm view`)*
+- **`@types/node` missing → `process.env` untyped.** Mitigation: add `@types/node` to
+  devDependencies and list it in `tsconfig.node.json`'s `types`. *(HIGH)*
+- **TS strict mode bites immediately.** `src/main.ts` is the first strict-mode stress test:
+  `document.getElementById` returns `HTMLElement | null`, so `as HTMLCanvasElement | null`
+  + null guard is required; `getContext('2d')` returns `CanvasRenderingContext2D | null` so
+  the `if (canvas && ctx)` narrowing is required. `noUncheckedIndexedAccess` does not bite
+  here (no index access) but will in ph.2's grid code — note it for the ph.2 researcher.
+  *(HIGH)*
+- **`import.meta.env.BASE_URL` typing requires `vite/client`.** Set via
+  `tsconfig.json` `types: ["vite/client"]`. Without it, `import.meta.env` is untyped and
+  any `BASE_URL` usage (ph.3+ level loading) won't compile. ph.1 doesn't use it yet but the
+  type reference must be in place from the start. *(HIGH)*
+- **`verbatimModuleSyntax: true` forces `import type`.** Every type-only import must use
+  `import type { ... }`. The smoke test imports `Direction` as a *value* (it's an enum, used
+  as a value `Direction.Up`), so `import { Direction }` is correct there. ph.2+ type-only
+  imports (`import type { Level }`) must use the `type` modifier or `tsc --noEmit` fails.
+  *(HIGH)*
+- **`vitest` default is watch mode.** `npm test` MUST use `vitest run` (or `vitest --run`),
+  not bare `vitest`, or CI hangs. *(HIGH — verified via `vitest --help`)*
+- **`const enum` + `isolatedModules` incompatibility.** Use a regular `enum` (or a union
+  type), not `const enum`, in `src/types.ts`. `isolatedModules: true` (required by Vite)
+  breaks cross-file `const enum` inlining. *(HIGH)*
+- **Windows / Unix path differences.** Use forward slashes everywhere (gitignore, globs,
+  `include` paths). Vitest's `environmentMatchGlobs` glob `'tests/**/*-dom.test.ts'` is
+  forward-slash and works cross-platform. *(HIGH)*
+- **Lockfile drift.** If `package.json` is edited (deps added/changed) without a
+  re-`npm install`, `package-lock.json` drifts and `npm ci` (used in ph.9 CI) fails. Rule:
+  any `package.json` edit must be immediately followed by `npm install` and the regenerated
+  lockfile committed in the same commit. *(HIGH)*
+- **`server.open: true` in headless contexts.** Do NOT enable it in ph.1; `npm run dev` is
+  run in CI/headless contexts and an auto-open would error or hang. *(HIGH)*
+- **happy-dom does not implement Canvas 2D.** Not a ph.1 issue (smoke test doesn't touch
+  canvas), but flagged for ph.3+: any unit test calling `getContext('2d').fillRect` under
+  happy-dom needs a `vi.stubGlobal`/spy mock. *(MEDIUM — verified in stack.md Direction 7a)*
+- **Vitest 4 vs Vitest 3 breaking changes.** Vitest 4 changed default pool to `forks`,
+  renamed some CLI flags, and tightened environment matching. The ph.1 config (`vitest run`,
+  `environmentMatchGlobs`, `include`) uses only stable, v4-present APIs verified via
+  `vitest --help`. No `pool` override needed (default `forks` is fine for one smoke test).
+  *(MEDIUM — API surface verified; deeper v3→v4 migration not relevant since ph.1 is greenfield)*
+
+---
+
+## TDD Implications
+
+- **The smoke test must pass from the moment `npm test` is runnable.** It is the ph.1
+  acceptance gate. Implementation order (step 10 above) places it after `src/types.ts`
+  exists so its `Direction` import resolves.
+- **The smoke test must NOT depend on any game-logic shape.** It asserts `1 + 1 === 2` and
+  `Direction.Up === 'up'` — pure constants. No `Grid`, no `GameState`, no `applyMove`. This
+  keeps it deletable: ph.2 replaces it with real reducer tests and removes
+  `smoke.test.ts` wholesale. The smoke test is scaffolding, not a foundation.
+- **The smoke test's `Direction` import is a real wiring check**, not a logic test. It
+  verifies that `tests/` can import from `src/` under Vitest 4's resolution — a ph.1 risk
+  (a broken `include` glob or missing root would surface here). This is the test's
+  load-bearing purpose beyond "Vitest boots".
+- **No DOM environment needed for the smoke test.** It runs under the default `node`
+  environment (per `vitest.config.ts`), so happy-dom is not exercised in ph.1. happy-dom is
+  installed and configured now so ph.2+'s `-dom.test.ts` files work without config churn.
+- **`npm run build` runs `tsc --noEmit` first.** This makes the build a type-check gate: a
+  type error fails `npm run build` before `vite build` emits. Treat the build as a second
+  test (type-level) that must stay green.
+- **No TDD red-green for ph.1 itself.** ph.1 is scaffolding (`type: config`/`scaffolding`
+  in plan terms), not behavior — there is no failing-test-first loop. The smoke test is a
+  sanity check, not a TDD driver. TDD red-green begins in ph.2 with the move reducer.
+- **Future ph.2 interaction.** ph.2 will: (a) delete `tests/unit/smoke.test.ts`, (b) add
+  `tests/unit/move.test.ts` with real reducer assertions, (c) likely add `-dom.test.ts`
+  files that exercise happy-dom. None of these require `vitest.config.ts` changes — the
+  `environmentMatchGlobs` convention handles (c) automatically by filename.
